
[1]repine

   REPI'NE, v.i. [re and pine.]

   1. To fret one's self; to be discontented; to feel inward discontent
   which preys on the spirits; with at or against. It is our duty never to
   repine at the allotments of Providence.

   2. To complain discontentedly; to murmur.

   Multitudes repine at the want of that which nothing but idleness
   hinders them from enjoying.

   3. To envy.
